    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen:\n\n1. `ui2` is enabled, and\n1. the 'ruler' option is set (the default), and\n1. the `MsgArea` highlight is defined\n\nThen setting 'winhighlight' in a floating window will make Neovim crash due to the following assertion error:\n\n```\n.../neovim/src/nvim/statusline.c:543: redraw_ruler: Assertion `attr == HL_ATTR(HLF_MSG)' failed.\n```\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThis reproduces the error with `nvim --clean`:\n\n```lua\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({})\nlocal win_opts = { relative = \"editor\", row = 1, col = 1, width = 20, height = 5 }\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(0, true, win_opts)\nvim.cmd([[hi! link MsgArea Normal]])\nvim.cmd([[setlocal winhighlight=Normal:WarningMsg]])\n```\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim doesn't crash.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-67+g164dfa1d5f   (but also reproduces with v0.12.0)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\n`neovim-nightly-bin` from AUR",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-08T16:02:36Z",
